			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>Property Probes: Source Code Based Exploration of Program Analysis Results</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AntonRisbergAlaküla.html">Anton Risberg Alaküla</a>, <a href="../profile/GörelHedin.html">Görel Hedin</a>, <a href="../profile/NiklasFors.html">Niklas Fors</a>, <a href="../profile/AdrianPop.html">Adrian Pop</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567525">10.1145/3567512.3567525</a></li>
<li>Original shorter version of <a href="../sle2024s/paper09.html"><em>Property probes: Live exploration of program analysis results</em></a> (SLE 2024 SI)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4f.html"><span class="tagM">T4F: Visualisation</span></a><ul><li> Property probes provide interactive visualization/exploration of program analysis results in source code.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It delivers tooling support to inspect and navigate analysis outcomes.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> The interface is designed to support developer comprehension and interactive investigation.
</li></ul></li></ul>
